review:
We visited this restaurant whilst on holiday, having pre booked an outside terrace table from the UK. It's a lovely spot, next to the city walls with views of the sea. Be prepared to pay for the experience, as it's expensive but it's worth it as a holiday memory and for the quality.
We opted for the 7 course taster menu, accompanied by a local wine and were not disappointed:
Food - high quality, perfectly presented; loved it all, especially the shrimp soup;
Wine - we went with a reasonably priced bottle of white, representative of the region, as recommended by the sommelier to accompany our taster menu;
Location/ambience - lovely romantic spot, with nice lighting on the castle and city walls when the sun goes down;
Service - I have to say our senior waiter for the evening was impeccable! ... knows his job, but equally, if not more important, made us feel welcome and at ease;
And finally, an unexpected surprise was when my partner returned to our table following a visit to the facilities, to tell me that the music and songs we'd been listening to through the terrace speakers all evening was not recorded, but live... the singer/musician was that good!
